01:21:27,801 --> 01:21:30,561
He said your accent is funny.

797
01:22:03,841 --> 01:22:05,841
Get down.

798
01:22:07,121 --> 01:22:09,121
Get down.

799
01:22:10,881 --> 01:22:11,861
Chinese. (African).

800
01:22:11,961 --> 01:22:13,961
Back.

801
01:22:25,161 --> 01:22:27,161
Back.

802
01:22:43,601 --> 01:22:45,631
Thank you Lara, for leading us here,

803
01:22:45,731 --> 01:22:47,991
and for finding the orb, in the first place.

804
01:22:48,091 --> 01:22:53,991
However, you have seen the exact position.
You could save me hours, days even.

805
01:22:54,091 --> 01:22:57,831
Help me, and I'll make
you worth your while.

806
01:22:58,641 --> 01:22:59,631
No.

807
01:22:59,731 --> 01:23:03,386
Think of what I'm offering you, let her go.

808
01:23:04,761 --> 01:23:07,591
The chance to find out,
how it all began,

809
01:23:07,691 --> 01:23:10,751
life line, the origin what we are...

810
01:23:11,121 --> 01:23:14,181
...don't tell me you're not tempted.

811
01:23:15,241 --> 01:23:17,876
That's like a Pandoran trouble.

812
01:23:17,921 --> 01:23:20,421
They told me you wouldn't do it.

813
01:23:20,521 --> 01:23:26,301
And I told them you would
rather than lose two of your closet friends.

814
01:23:27,001 --> 01:23:28,781
There goes the Cradle of Life.

815
01:23:28,881 --> 01:23:30,881
Sorry, Lara.

816
01:23:31,321 --> 01:23:34,636
It's your destiny to see what's inside.

817
01:23:35,801 --> 01:23:39,626
He's right, it's just beyond
the canyon, remember?

818
01:23:40,000 --> 01:23:42,654
Such a short walk
might save your friends.

819
01:23:47,000 --> 01:23:51,500
Well, if it spares my friends...
I'm up for a walk.

820
01:24:25,681 --> 01:24:27,231
I'm sure she'd understand.
Do you have a plan?

821
01:24:27,331 --> 01:24:29,351
You should've just told Lara
we were hostage.

822
01:24:29,451 --> 01:24:32,256
Reiss would never have found out.

823
01:24:45,241 --> 01:24:50,021
I don't suppose either of you
know how to fly a helicopter?

824
01:24:50,121 --> 01:24:51,661
I can.

825
01:24:51,761 --> 01:24:52,591
What?

826
01:24:52,691 --> 01:24:54,581
What?

827
01:24:54,681 --> 01:24:59,961
I've got over 150 hours between flight 
simulation...games,... models...

828
01:25:00,521 --> 01:25:02,816
...and then the real thing?

829
01:25:03,561 --> 01:25:04,421
Two.

830
01:25:04,521 --> 01:25:09,231
Two? well, you're only gonna fly it once I'm out,
so remember your two hours well!

831
01:25:09,331 --> 01:25:12,731
I hope you remember your two hours well.

832
01:25:44,161 --> 01:25:46,841
- It's through here? 
- Um.

833
01:25:48,601 --> 01:25:50,601
Move, baby.

834
01:27:15,881 --> 01:27:17,881
What's that?

835
01:27:18,441 --> 01:27:20,441
You. Check it out.

836
01:27:24,241 --> 01:27:26,241
Keep moving.

837
01:28:09,041 --> 01:28:10,221
What are you doing?

838
01:28:10,321 --> 01:28:12,321
Back in formation, now.

839
01:29:02,721 --> 01:29:04,721
Holy shit.

840
01:29:05,641 --> 01:29:08,871
Don't. They seem to react to movement.

841
01:29:26,361 --> 01:29:28,361
They're gone.

842
01:29:30,561 --> 01:29:33,381
I know we're close, I've seen it in your eyes.

843
01:29:33,481 --> 01:29:35,471
Take me to Pandora's Box.

844
01:29:35,571 --> 01:29:37,181
I don't know how.

845
01:29:37,281 --> 01:29:39,281
Do it now.

846
01:29:40,761 --> 01:29:44,301
Well you were the one who
wanted to go for a walk.

847
01:29:44,401 --> 01:29:46,401
So start walking.

848
01:29:52,161 --> 01:29:54,541
The next one will be higher.

849
01:30:31,241 --> 01:30:34,386
only with the orb can it be revealed.

850
01:30:35,561 --> 01:30:38,706
only with the orb can it be revealed.

851
01:30:41,881 --> 01:30:44,346
All right, I'll need the orb.

852
01:30:45,761 --> 01:30:48,981
Do you want to see
the Cradle of Life or not?

853
01:30:49,081 --> 01:30:51,716
You tell me what to do with it.

854
01:31:46,801 --> 01:31:49,181
Don't think you could outwit me, Croft.

855
01:31:49,281 --> 01:31:51,281
Oh, do shut up.

856
01:31:53,081 --> 01:31:55,631
So this is the Cradle of Life.

857
01:32:03,201 --> 01:32:05,201
Here they are.

858
01:32:06,161 --> 01:32:08,966
It's all yours.  Time to be a hero.

859
01:33:10,481 --> 01:33:12,481
There it is.

860
01:33:23,281 --> 01:33:25,021
Perfect, isn't it?

861
01:33:25,121 --> 01:33:27,871
All that power in such a banal container.

862
01:33:27,971 --> 01:33:30,991
Legend tells it when Pandora
saw inside the box...

863
01:33:31,091 --> 01:33:34,021
...she cried a pool of a black acid for tears...

864
01:33:34,121 --> 01:33:37,521
...and, as it was a woman
who found the box,...

865
01:33:37,521 --> 01:33:40,921
...I see no reason to break with tradition.

866
01:33:40,961 --> 01:33:43,596
A woman should collect the box.

867
01:33:45,641 --> 01:33:47,641
Go on.

868
01:33:50,481 --> 01:33:52,606
It's impossible to reach.

869
01:33:54,481 --> 01:33:56,481
Now, take it.

870
01:33:57,361 --> 01:33:59,361
Take it.

871
01:35:25,401 --> 01:35:27,441
I don't think so, Reiss.

872
01:36:20,321 --> 01:36:22,321
Are you okay?

873
01:36:22,641 --> 01:36:25,161
- I'm fine, fine. 
- There you go.

874
01:36:32,281 --> 01:36:34,061
You've come prepared.

875
01:36:34,161 --> 01:36:36,881
Well, I know how clumsy you are.

876
01:36:40,241 --> 01:36:42,451
How are Hillary and Bryce?

877
01:36:43,481 --> 01:36:45,481
They are fighting.

878
01:36:59,361 --> 01:37:01,181
Thank you.

879
01:37:01,281 --> 01:37:03,101
What was that?

880
01:37:03,201 --> 01:37:05,201
Oh.

881
01:37:06,001 --> 01:37:08,001
Thank you.

882
01:37:19,721 --> 01:37:21,721
Let's get out of here.

883
01:37:31,641 --> 01:37:33,641
Terry.

884
01:37:34,081 --> 01:37:36,081
What are you doing?

885
01:37:36,121 --> 01:37:38,416
Well, you're joking, right?

886
01:37:39,281 --> 01:37:42,596
We're taking this with us,
this is ours.

887
01:37:43,561 --> 01:37:47,301
You're not walking out of here
with that box.

888
01:37:48,081 --> 01:37:51,111
So, what are you saying,
we'll just leave it?

889
01:37:51,211 --> 01:37:52,771
Well, it's worth a fortune.

890
01:37:52,871 --> 01:37:55,761
Put it back.
- No, I don't think so.

891
01:37:55,921 --> 01:37:58,831
It could kill millions of innocent people.

892
01:37:58,931 --> 01:38:00,391
Now you're being romantic.

893
01:38:00,491 --> 01:38:03,361
Put it back.
- No.

894
01:38:06,081 --> 01:38:09,501
I've helped you keep this away from Reiss.

895
01:38:09,601 --> 01:38:11,601
This is my reward.

896
01:38:12,081 --> 01:38:14,361
I'm taking it with me.

897
01:38:24,281 --> 01:38:26,661
So it's come to this, has it?

898
01:38:26,761 --> 01:38:30,331
Well you do have authorization to kill me.

899
01:38:31,761 --> 01:38:33,581
You'd better do it, then.

900
01:38:33,681 --> 01:38:39,291
'Cause if you think standing
in front of me is gonna be enough...

901
01:38:41,001 --> 01:38:44,061
You don't have it in you to stop me.

902
01:38:51,961 --> 01:38:54,171
See, all your beliefs...

903
01:38:54,921 --> 01:38:56,921
...all your ideals,...

904
01:38:57,721 --> 01:38:59,721
They're not real.

905
01:38:59,761 --> 01:39:00,861
I am.

906
01:39:00,961 --> 01:39:02,961
And you've loved me.

907
01:39:06,401 --> 01:39:08,351
I don't know how strong you think you are...

908
01:39:08,451 --> 01:39:12,361
...but you're not going
to choose them over me.

909
01:39:15,521 --> 01:39:17,101
No move?

910
01:39:17,201 --> 01:39:19,201
No.

911
01:39:21,801 --> 01:39:23,801
Thanks.

912
01:41:44,961 --> 01:41:46,961
The box is safe now.

913
01:41:49,521 --> 01:41:52,751
Some things are not meant to be found.

914
01:42:02,441 --> 01:42:05,221
Did you ever do anything the easy way?

915
01:42:05,321 --> 01:42:08,211
I wouldn't want to disappoint you.

916
01:42:31,881 --> 01:42:32,911
Larie, are you okay?

917
01:42:33,011 --> 01:42:34,261
Lara, are you all right?

918
01:42:34,361 --> 01:42:36,921
This is...very touching.

919
01:42:37,321 --> 01:42:41,672
You know us, always making
friends, having a laugh.

920
01:42:41,772 --> 01:42:43,772
getting married.

921
01:42:44,401 --> 01:42:46,401
What?

922
01:42:46,881 --> 01:42:50,421
This is a wedding ceremony,
and you are the grooms.

923
01:42:50,521 --> 01:42:52,521
Good luck, boys.

924
01:42:52,961 --> 01:42:55,001
Sanke, Asante.

925
01:42:55,521 --> 01:42:57,761
Asante, asante.

926
01:43:09,201 --> 01:43:11,201
Go.

